# health-mcp environment variables (all optional)

# Override the default DuckDB location (~/.claude/health-mcp/health.duckdb).
# HEALTH_MCP_DB=~/.claude/health-mcp/health.duckdb

# Default host/port for Health Auto Export TCP live mode.
# Tools accept host/port arguments per call, so these are only fallbacks.
# HEALTH_AUTO_EXPORT_HOST=localhost
# HEALTH_AUTO_EXPORT_PORT=9000

# --- Google Health API (successor to Fitbit Web API / Google Fit, retired Sept 2026) ---
# Set up a Google Cloud project + OAuth Web-Server client, run the OAuth flow
# once, then export these. Run health_vendor_setup_guide('google_health') for
# the full walkthrough. NOTE: publish the OAuth app to Production or the refresh
# token expires after 7 days (Testing-status limit) and daily sync breaks.
# GOOGLE_HEALTH_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# GOOGLE_HEALTH_REFRESH_TOKEN=
# GOOGLE_HEALTH_CLIENT_ID=
# GOOGLE_HEALTH_CLIENT_SECRET=

# --- Oura ---
# OURA_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# --- Fitbit (DEPRECATED — Web API retired Sept 2026; use Google Health above) ---
# FITBIT_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# FITBIT_REFRESH_TOKEN=
# FITBIT_CLIENT_ID=
# FITBIT_CLIENT_SECRET=
